Array
-----
1. Array is a non primitive datatype(Reference Type).
2. Array is a collection of homogenous data elements(same type of elements).
3. Array works on the concept of indexing and array indexing always starts from zero because it follows number system.
4. Prerequisitie for array allocation is base address.
5. Array works on continuous memory allocation.
6. Array elements shares same name but differentiable by there indexing.
7. Array are object in java.
8. Arrays are dynamically allocated in java.
9. Arrays can hold primitive datatype elements as well as object reference.
10. Types of array: 
    a. one dimensional array (1d array)
    b. two dimensional array (2d array)
    c. multi dimensional array

One dimensional array :
Syntax I : 
<datatype> <array_name> [] = {element1, element2, element3 ,.....}; 
example : int arr[] = {1,2,3,4,5};

Syntax II : 
<datatype> <array_name> [] = new <datatype>[]{element1, element2, element3 ,.....}; 
example : int arr[] = new int[]{1,2,3,4,5};

Syntax III : 
<datatype> <array_name> [] = new <datatype>[size]; 
example : int arr[] = new int[5];
